<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">May 20, 2024</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-may-20-2024/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-237374 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/columbiagaza-150x150.jpeg" alt="columbia gaza" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.thenation.com/article/society/columbia-student-journalist-repression/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Six student journalists at Columbia discuss what they’ve learned while covering the protests</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.publicbooks.org/we-were-not-that-band-but-what-was-sonic-youth/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">What Thurston Moore’s new memoir adds to a fan’s understanding of Sonic Youth</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/16/t-magazine/nuns-film-immaculate-doubt-new-boy.html" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">On the literary and cinematic representations of nuns</span></a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-may-20-2024/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
